      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For suspicious losses like theft or unexplained discrepancies, maritime law requires a thorough investigation, often involving the carrier and port authorities, rather than just relying on standard weather clauses. If theft is suspected, a formal police report would be crucial evidence for any insurance claim to be valid. Ultimately, the insurance policy dictates the coverage for perils beyond standard maritime risks, so review your CIF insurance terms carefully.",
